4:
You there. Come out of the
shadows. What do you want from
me?
5:
...Sorry. I didn't mean to startle you.
I'll come out now.
8:
I'm a traveler. I saw your campfire,
and... I just wanted some company,
that's all.
11:
Why would a traveler be out here
away from the roads? If you're
looking for Tiatha, you should
venture south.
14:
I'm not traveling to Tiatha, actually.
My destination is a village just north
of here.
17:
So you're here to subdue the bandits
as well? They didn't mention hiring
others for the job...
24:
So, the village was overrun by
mountain bandits, and they're still in
control...
27:
...And you, Charla, are going to take
it back?
30:
Indeed. I am a mage, hired by the
city of Tiatha to eradicate said
bandits.
32:
But what brings you here, Alk? It
seems you've gone to great lengths
to find this humble village...
36:
I'm researching the local geology
and flora. I was hoping they would
have what I was looking for, but... I
guess I should've done more
groundwork.
39:
Say, Charla—would you mind giving
me a hand? This is very, very
important to me.
42:
And if it's about my right eye, don't
worry. Even with one eye, I can hold
my own—and I guarantee I'm better
than your average fighter.
45:
That's quite some confidence you've
got there. Defeating the bandits will
be easy; it's the aftermath that will
prove difficult.
47:
This has happened before. Several
times, in fact. In a few years, the
bandits will appear again. Do you
know why?
50:
...Because the villagers don't know
how to fight?
53:
...It's a poor village. Ignoring it would
prove disadvantageous to a Tiatha,
but that's all it would be—a minor
risk.
54:
Sooner or later, another desperate
villager will turn to brigandry... and
the cycle continues.
56: Someone needs to break that cycle.
58:
My apologies. It's none of your
concern, I know. Let us rest and
prepare for tomorrow.
67:
O Great Fire, dauntless fury of the
stars! Reduce my enemies to cinder!
75:
..."You can't say"? What do you
mean?!
77:
These thugs are nothing but pawns,
we must kill the leader of their band.
Tell me where they are! Now!
79: Eeek! P-please... have mercy on us!
82:
That's enough, Charla... There are
other ways to find out where the
bandits are hiding.
85:
...You're right. It's only a matter of
time before we find them. Despite
that, these villagers are too
cowardly to break their silence.
93:
It's not that they don't know how to
fight—it's that they don't possess the
WILL!
95:
If they can't act on their wills,
perhaps they don't need them at all!
96:
O darkness... Fill these hollow hearts
with your power!
101: A cryptic artifact?! But, this power...
104:
You weren't here for research at all,
were you? You knew. You came
looking for this artifact—or perhaps
for us?
107:
What are you planning to do with
that, Charla?
110:
I told you already. I am here to
eradicate those bandits! And I will
give the villagers the strength to do
it!
113:
Can't you see that they're terrified
by what you're doing?!
116:
That fear is the VERY thing that
prevents them from acting! It has no
place in this world. It is weakness.
117:
I shall replace it with a "will" of my
own.
123:
Don't tell me you can't understand
how they feel.
127:
Afraid, cowering against tyranny,
begging for help... They know they're
weak—and wish they weren't!
138:
You wanted to show them that they
weren't alone... You wanted to fight
alongside them! That's why you
came back home, isn't it?
140:
You of all people should know how
they feel. You should be able to hear
their hearts crying out!
143:
Shut up... SHUT UP! I'm going to save
them—save EVERYONE!
146:
No, you won't! You'll only end up
more alone than ever.
149:
Stars, give me strength!
Diastral Blade!
153: ...But I won't let you do that!
161:
Hey... Wake up! You, you're Charles,
aren't you? It's me, don't you
remember?!
165:
Yes, I knew that you were a Star
Augur. But I wasn't lying when I said I
was conducting research.
168:
Excuse me, everyone! I would like to
ask for a bit of your time, if you don't
mind!
171:
Would anyone be interested in
making a new type of curry—and
curry spices—with me?
174:
I'm planning a sort of joint project
between Palpebra and Tiatha. I was
hoping that you would help serve as
the project's pilot case.
180:
Let's make some money together,
shall we?
186:
I see! I suppose everything went
swimmingly, then?
190:
Yep! I finally managed to source all
of the ingredients that we were
missing. Now we can finally make
Shibuya curry!
194: I can't wait to try it.
199:
Here he comes. This should've been
his fifth outing by now. I have no
doubt he'll have worked up quite the
appetite.
203:
Nimbus! Long time, no see! You want
some curry?
208:
What the? Curry? That sounds...
...like the best idea you've had in a
while. Let's get to eatin'!
